  author={null},
  abstract={A first search for the \(\Xi_{bc}^{+} \to J/\psi \Xi_{c}^{+}\) decay is performed by the LHCb experiment with a 
            data sample of proton-proton collisions, corresponding to an integrated luminosity of \(9~\rm{fb}^{-1}\) recorded 
            at centre-of-mass energies of \(7\), \(8\), and \(13~\rm{TeV}\). Two peaking structures are seen with a local 
